'''Air Comores International''' was an [[airline]] based in [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]], [[Comoros]]. It operated international services providing long-haul flights to [[France]] and the [[Middle East]], as well as regional services to eastern and southern [[Africa]] and the [[Indian Ocean]]. 

== History ==
The airline was established in 2004 and started operations in November 2004. It is owned by the Government of Comoros (60%) and [[Air Bourbon]] (40%).  The airline ceased operations in 2006.

== Services ==
Air Comores International operated services to the following international scheduled destinations (at December 2006): [[Antananarivo]], [[Dar es Salaam]], [[Dubai]], [[Johannesburg]], [[Majunga]], [[Marseille]], [[Mayotte]], [[Mauritius]], [[Mombasa]], [[Nairobi]], [[Nosy Be]], [[Paris-Orly]], [[St Pierre de la Reunion]] and [[Zanzibar]].<br>
The airline also served the following scheduled domestic destinations (at December 2006): [[Anjouan]] and [[Moheli]].

== Fleet ==
The Air Comores International fleet consisted of (at September 2006):
*1 [[Boeing 737-400]]
*1 [[Boeing 767-300ER]]

